# Design System

## Design Token System (MANDATORY FOR NEW COMPONENTS)

Always import and use design tokens instead of raw class strings:

```tsx
import { tokens } from '@/lib/design-tokens';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// Page title
<h1 className={tokens.heading.page}>Revenue</h1>

// Section header
<h2 className={tokens.heading.section}>Overview</h2>

// Card title
<h3 className={tokens.heading.card}>Top Performers</h3>

// Stat value
<p className={tokens.stat.large}>$12,400</p>

// Body text
<p className={tokens.body.muted}>Last updated 2 hours ago</p>

// Conditional layering with cn()
<h3 className={cn(tokens.heading.card, isActive && 'text-primary')}>

// Empty states
<div className={tokens.empty.container}>
  <Package className={tokens.empty.icon} />
  <h3 className={tokens.empty.heading}>No items found</h3>
  <p className={tokens.empty.description}>Try adjusting your filters</p>
</div>
```

Available token groups: `heading`, `body`, `label`, `stat`, `card`, `layout`, `status`, `empty`, `loading`.

### Card Tokens (MANDATORY)
```tsx
import { tokens } from '@/lib/design-tokens';

// Card wrapper (rounded + shadow)
<Card className={tokens.card.wrapper}>

// Icon box in card header
<div className={tokens.card.iconBox}>
  <Brain className={tokens.card.icon} />
</div>

// Card title
<CardTitle className={tokens.card.title}>CARD NAME</CardTitle>
```

Use `getTokenFor('page-title')` helper when unsure which token to use.

## Typography Rules (HARD RULES)

### BANNED Classes (cause synthetic bolding)
- `font-bold` (700) -- BANNED
- `font-semibold` (600) -- BANNED
- `font-extrabold` (800) -- BANNED
- `font-black` (900) -- BANNED

Maximum allowed weight: `font-medium` (500)

### ALLOWED Classes
- `font-light` (300)
- `font-normal` (400)
- `font-medium` (500) -- MAXIMUM

### Font Families
| Class | Font | Usage | Rules |
|-------|------|-------|-------|
| `font-display` | Termina | Headlines, buttons, stats, navigation | Always uppercase, wide tracking (0.08em) |
| `font-sans` | Aeonik Pro | Body text, paragraphs, UI labels | NEVER uppercase |
| `font-serif` | Laguna | Editorial accents | Bold weight available |
| `font-script` | Sloop Script | Decorative elements | Use sparingly |

### Emphasis Without Bold

When you need visual hierarchy:
- Use `font-display` for headlines (automatic uppercase + tracking)
- Increase font size (`text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`)
- Use color contrast (`text-foreground` vs `text-muted-foreground`)
- Add letter-spacing (`tracking-wide`, `tracking-wider`)
- Use borders or backgrounds for visual separation

## Theme System

HSL CSS variables. Available themes:
- **Cream** (default) -- Light cream palette
- **Rose** -- Blush pink pastel
- **Sage** -- Mint green pastel
- **Ocean** -- Soft blue pastel
- **Platform** -- Purple/violet fintech-inspired (platform admin only)

Semantic colors: `primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `destructive`, `success`, `oat`, `gold`

## Component Styling

- Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge Tailwind classes
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- Dashboard content: `<div className="px-8 py-8 max-w-[1600px] mx-auto">`

## Loading States

Spinner (full page):
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-center h-64">
  <Loader2 className={tokens.loading.spinner} />
</div>
```

Skeleton (tables/cards):
```tsx
{[1, 2, 3, 4, 5].map((i) => (
  <Skeleton key={i} className={tokens.loading.skeleton} />
))}
```

